cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR. 

This paper is about developing methods to overcome catastrophic forgetting during fine-tuning of neural comprehension models for domain adaptation in reading comprehension. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and understanding. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper involves the development of new data sets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
